# OSLIFE · environment variables & secrets reference
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# RULE: never commit real secrets. This file only contains the public anon key
# (safe by design — RLS protects the data) and placeholders for everything else.
#
# Project: Supabase "oslife" (nhyunnnmdcmojvkxrbpl, eu-west-1) · Vercel "oslife"
# This is the ONLY backend OSLIFE talks to — no rick-os / Vercel middleman.
#
# Where each value actually lives:
#   Frontend    → Vercel dashboard (or .env.local locally — git-ignored)
#   Apps Script → Script Properties in script.google.com (per project)
#   Edge Fn     → Supabase → Edge Functions → Manage secrets

# ── 1. Frontend (Vite / Vercel) ───────────────────────────────────────────────
# anon key: Supabase dashboard → nhyunnnmdcmojvkxrbpl → Settings → API → anon/public
VITE_SUPABASE_URL=https://nhyunnnmdcmojvkxrbpl.supabase.co
VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=<anon key from Supabase dashboard → nhyunnnmdcmojvkxrbpl → Settings → API>
VITE_TELEGRAM_BOT_USERNAME=<bot username without @, from @BotFather — not secret>

# ── 2. Supabase Edge Function secrets ─────────────────────────────────────────
# Supabase → Project nhyunnnmdcmojvkxrbpl → Edge Functions → Manage secrets.
# (SUPABASE_URL and SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY are auto-injected — don't add them.)
#
#   OSLIFE_USER_ID          <auth.users uuid of your account>   (legacy name RICK_USER_ID still read as a fallback)
#   NOTION_TOKEN            <Notion internal integration secret — notion.so → Settings → Integrations>
#   SYNC_SECRET             <random 32+ char secret — openssl rand -base64 32>   (cron caller for notion-sync; optional for notion-mutate)
#   INGEST_SECRET           <random 32+ char secret>   (shared with the Sheet-bound Apps Scripts)
#   WALLET_WEBHOOK_SECRET   <random 32+ char secret>   (MacroDroid → wallet-ingest; phone-events-ingest
#                            and weight-ingest fall back to this too — same phone, one secret is enough)
#   PHONE_WEBHOOK_SECRET    <random 32+ char secret>   (MacroDroid → phone-events-ingest AND
#                            weight-ingest; both fall back to WALLET_WEBHOOK_SECRET if unset)
#   WEIGHT_WEBHOOK_SECRET   <random 32+ char secret>   (optional — only if weight-ingest should use
#                            its own secret instead of PHONE_WEBHOOK_SECRET)
#   GBK_API_KEY             <Geldrop Buurtkaart admin → API key (header X-GBK-Key)>
#   GBK_BASE_URL            https://www.geldropbuurtkaart.nl   (optional; this is the default)
#   ANTHROPIC_API_KEY       <console.anthropic.com → API keys>   (optional — HEYRA's agents and the
#                            Reflect narrative fall back to the existing rule-based text without it)
#   TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN      <@BotFather → /newbot → token>   (notify-tick + telegram-webhook)
#   TELEGRAM_WEBHOOK_SECRET <random 32+ char secret>   (given to setWebhook as secret_token; Telegram
#                            echoes it back as header X-Telegram-Bot-Api-Secret-Token — telegram-webhook)
#   BRAINDUMP_WORKER_URL   <public base URL of the braindump media worker>   (optional — enables real
#                            video/audio transcription; without it, media falls back to metadata-only)
#   WORKER_SECRET          <random 32+ char secret>   (bearer the braindump-ingest fn sends to the worker;
#                            must match the worker's WORKER_SECRET — see integrations/braindump-worker/)
#   GROQ_API_KEY           <console.groq.com API key>   (Whisper transcription; lives on the WORKER, not
#                            the edge fn — listed here for completeness)
#   CRON_SECRET             <random 32+ char secret>   (bearer token the pg_cron job sends to
#                            notify-tick; also pasted literally into the one-time cron.schedule() SQL
#                            — not stored anywhere else, never commit the filled-in SQL)
#
# Edge Function URLs (base https://nhyunnnmdcmojvkxrbpl.supabase.co/functions/v1/):
#   notion-sync              ← projects + clients READ  (Notion → Supabase)
#   notion-mutate            ← projects/clients WRITE   (app → Notion)        [verify_jwt]
#   notion-hq                ← side-business HQ callouts (Buurtkaart/Eyes/Dakmeester)
#   gbk-overview             ← Geldrop Buurtkaart WordPress API proxy          [verify_jwt]
#   health-sheets-ingest     ← Health sheet → health_* tables
#   payments-sheet-ingest    ← Betalingen sheet → finance_tx
#   screentime-sheet-ingest  ← Schermtijd sheet → screentime
#   wallet-ingest            ← payment notifications (MacroDroid: Wallet or bank apps) → finance_tx
#   phone-events-ingest      ← unlock/screen-off (MacroDroid) → phone_events, health_sleep, screentime_daily.pickups
#   weight-ingest            ← scale-app notification (MacroDroid, experimental) → health_body_metrics
#   heyra-brain              ← Claude API proxy for HEYRA's agents + Reflect narrative [verify_jwt]
#   categorize-vendor        ← Haiku + web search: tags a merchant's category/domain (vendor cache) [verify_jwt]
#   braindump-ingest         ← Braindump v2: shared item → Markdown note (text/link/image/pdf/social) [verify_jwt]
#                              (media is delegated to the braindump-worker — integrations/braindump-worker/)
#   notify-tick              ← scheduled brain: composes + sends Telegram nudges  [no verify_jwt, CRON_SECRET bearer]
#   telegram-webhook         ← receives Telegram updates (/start, button taps)    [no verify_jwt, secret_token header]

# ── 3. Apps Script — ONE standalone project ("OSLIFE ingest") ─────────────────
# Create it at script.google.com → New project (NOT bound to a sheet). Add the
# files from integrations/apps-script/ (Code.gs + health-sheets.gs +
# payments-sheet.gs + screentime-sheet.gs). The sheet readers open your sheets
# BY ID, so you never touch the scripts that fill those sheets.
# Project Settings → Script Properties:
#   SUPABASE_URL          https://nhyunnnmdcmojvkxrbpl.supabase.co
#   SUPABASE_SERVICE_KEY  <service_role key — Supabase → Settings → API>
#   OSLIFE_USER_ID        <auth.users uuid>            (legacy RICK_USER_ID still works)
#   NOTION_TOKEN          <Notion integration secret>
#   NOTION_DB_ID          239ddc8e-9208-8186-b452-cc35f89677ff   (Projects DB)
#   NOTION_CLIENTS_DB_ID  239ddc8e-9208-8102-86b9-eda32f63e815   (Clients DB)
#   PAYMENTS_CAL_ID       <your payments Google Calendar id>
#   INGEST_SECRET         <same value as the edge-function secret>
#   HEALTH_SYNC_URL       https://nhyunnnmdcmojvkxrbpl.supabase.co/functions/v1/health-sheets-ingest
#   HEALTH_SHEET_ID       <id from the Health sheet URL>
#   PAYMENTS_SYNC_URL     https://nhyunnnmdcmojvkxrbpl.supabase.co/functions/v1/payments-sheet-ingest
#   PAYMENTS_SHEET_ID     <id from the Betalingen sheet URL>
#   SCREENTIME_SYNC_URL   https://nhyunnnmdcmojvkxrbpl.supabase.co/functions/v1/screentime-sheet-ingest
#   SCREENTIME_SHEET_ID   <id from the Schermtijd sheet URL>
# A sheet id is the long code in its URL:
#   https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/<THIS_IS_THE_ID>/edit
# Then run installAllTriggers() once and authorize the scopes.

# ── 4. Telegram bot (proactive notifications) — one-time setup ────────────────
# Create the bot, set the three secrets above, deploy notify-tick +
# telegram-webhook, register the webhook, and schedule the pg_cron tick.
# Full ordered checklist: docs/SECRETS.md → "Telegram-meldingen: eenmalige setup".
